# TABLE

A table is a collection of rows and columns.

---

# COLUMN (FIELD)

Represents an attribute of the data.

---

# ROW (RECORD)

Represents a single entry in the table.

---

# CHAR vs VARCHAR

char(n)

* Fixed length
* Adds extra spaces

Example:
Manoj -> [M][a][n][o][j][ ][ ][ ][ ][ ]

varchar(n)

* Variable length
* Uses only required space

Example:
Manoj -> [M][a][n][o][j]

